INSERT INTO `articles_mask` (`post`,`native_id`,`post_account_id`,`post_type`) VALUES ("Landing at Palm Beach International Airport, I was ready to see how the other half lived.µThe COVID-sane half, that is.µ<br/><br/> Our family hadn’t left New York since March.µWe had read about how Florida was able to maintain a case rate similar to or lower than New York’s while shunning our crippling lockdowns.µStill, we were apprehensive.µ\"Be careful down there, no one wears a mask,\" was typical of advice I got from well-meaning friends.µ<br/><br/> And indeed, Florida has a reputation as one of the looser states.µIn mid-April, after a short lockdown, Gov. Ron DeSantis gave the green light for beaches to open.µ\"Wait two weeks!µ\" the naysayers urged back then.µBut two weeks came and went, and Florida’s numbers remained relatively steady after a peak in mid-July.","1820656643","1","2");
INSERT INTO `articles_mask` (`post`,`native_id`,`post_account_id`,`post_type`) VALUES ("And indeed, Florida has a reputation as one of the looser states.µIn mid-April, after a short lockdown, Gov. Ron DeSantis gave the green light for beaches to open.µ\"Wait two weeks!µ\" the naysayers urged back then.µBut two weeks came and went, and Florida’s numbers remained relatively steady after a peak in mid-July.µ<br/><br/> Stepping off the plane, we noticed something odd: Everyone was, in fact, masked.µAnd keeping their distance.µThere was hand sanitizer everywhere.µThe COVID \"Mad Max\" world was nowhere to be found.µYes, everything was open, but precautions-wise, southern Florida looked a lot like New York.µ<br/><br/> FLORIDA 'NOT WASTING VACCINE' LIKE NEW YORK, PRIORITIZING ELDERLY: LT. GOV. JEANETTE NUNEZ","1820656643","1","2");
INSERT INTO `articles_mask` (`post`,`native_id`,`post_account_id`,`post_type`) VALUES ("FLORIDA 'NOT WASTING VACCINE' LIKE NEW YORK, PRIORITIZING ELDERLY: LT. GOV. JEANETTE NUNEZ <br/><br/> The main difference: Masks aren’t worn in no-risk situations.µIn Gotham, it’s very common to see people masked even when all alone on empty streets.µSmall children wear masks outside.µIn Florida, we saw maskless children playing together outside.µIt looked like the Before Times.µ<br/><br/> Which is a good thing: We act like it’s no big deal to wear masks even where risk is nonexistent.µBut, of course, it does matter.","1820656643","1","2");
INSERT INTO `articles_mask` (`post`,`native_id`,`post_account_id`,`post_type`) VALUES ("The main difference: Masks aren’t worn in no-risk situations.µIn Gotham, it’s very common to see people masked even when all alone on empty streets.µSmall children wear masks outside.µIn Florida, we saw maskless children playing together outside.µIt looked like the Before Times.µ<br/><br/> Which is a good thing: We act like it’s no big deal to wear masks even where risk is nonexistent.µBut, of course, it does matter.µ<br/><br/> In Florida, we saw the smiling faces of strangers for the first time in nine months.µIt’s hard to overstate how much that mattered to our well-being and the feeling of normality.","1820656643","1","2");
INSERT INTO `articles_mask` (`post`,`native_id`,`post_account_id`,`post_type`) VALUES ("In Florida, we saw the smiling faces of strangers for the first time in nine months.µIt’s hard to overstate how much that mattered to our well-being and the feeling of normality.µ<br/><br/> There’s also the element of pandemic fatigue: Wearing a mask all the time, even when unnecessary, will at some point discourage use when it actually matters.µ<br/><br/> CLICK HERE TO GET THE OPINION NEWSLETTER","1820656643","1","2");
